{
  "text": "These groups also provided opportunities to give and receive emotional support, further reinforcing the idea of reciprocity. This reciprocity helped the people affected by aphasia (both PWA and their families) to feel valued and gave them a sense of purpose. Helping others, not only being helped is significant for boosting well-being [CITATION_1] . In addition, participants described personal attributes that facilitated them to live successfully with aphasia. The power of positivity (Brown et al, 2012) , determination [CITATION_2] being . In our study, PWA and their family members identified a variety of resources, both internal and external, that could be built upon and reinforced.",
